OL,6,FAdd to the toxic mix, the current BBC
OL,7,Fchairman and the fact the
OL,8,Fdirector-general was active in local
OL,9,FConservative politics 30 years ago and
OL,10,Fyou can see the perfect recipe for
OL,11,Fconspiracy theorists.
OL,13,FAnyone with even a rudimentary
OL,14,Funderstanding of how the BBC works will
OL,15,Fbe aware of how the chairman is well
OL,16,Fremoved from editorial and creative
OL,17,Fdecision-making.
OL,19,FSimilar claims were made in the past
OL,20,Fabout governments sending in chairmen
OL,21,Fto "sort out" the BBC ` from Lord Hill
OL,22,Fto Marmaduke Hussey.
OL,3,CImpartiality and the BBC in the age of
OL,4,Csocial media
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G6/10
