OL,6,FBut somehow the BBC has to enjoy the
OL,7,Fconfidence of everyone in the land `
OL,8,Fthrough all shades of mainstream
OL,9,Fpolitical opinion and beyond.
OL,11,FTo say it can be a challenge and a
OL,12,Fnightmare is an understatement.
OL,14,FFor some critics, the fact a story did
OL,15,Fnot run on the BBC News at Six means
OL,16,Fthe BBC itself did not or would not
OL,17,Fcover it ` even if that story actually
OL,18,Fran on, say, the News at Ten or
OL,19,Ffeatured prominently online.
OL,3,CImpartiality and the BBC in the age of
OL,4,Csocial media
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G7/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
