OL,6,FOthers imagine preconceived left or
OL,7,Fright wing bias, misinterpret
OL,8,Finclusivity as wokeness, see a concern
OL,9,Fto attract younger audiences to some
OL,10,Fservices as meaning that older people
OL,11,Fdon't matter. The list goes on.
OL,13,FIn the meantime, the review of the
OL,14,FBBC's social media guidelines will get
OL,15,Funderway in earnest.
OL,17,FHopefully any reasonable person will be
OL,18,Fable to distinguish between those who
OL,19,Fappear on BBC programmes and those who
OL,20,Fmight be seen as representing the BBC
OL,21,Fitself.
OL,3,CImpartiality and the BBC in the age of
OL,4,Csocial media
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G8/10
